  "body": "* viper Version: 0.0.2\r\n* pyethereum Version: 2.1.0\r\n* OS: mac os\r\n* Python Version (python --version): 3.6.0\r\n* Environment (output of `pip freeze`):\r\n```shell\r\nargh==0.26.2\r\nasn1crypto==0.23.0\r\nastroid==1.5.3\r\nattrs==17.3.0\r\nbitcoin==1.1.42\r\nbumpversion==0.5.3\r\ncertifi==2017.4.17\r\ncffi==1.10.0\r\nchardet==3.0.4\r\nclick==6.7\r\ncoincurve==6.0.0\r\ncolorama==0.3.9\r\ncoverage==4.4.1\r\ncoveralls==1.1\r\ncytoolz==0.8.2\r\ndecorator==4.1.2\r\ndocopt==0.6.2\r\neth-testrpc==1.3.3\r\nethereum==2.1.0\r\nethereum-abi-utils==0.4.4\r\nethereum-keyfile==0.3.0\r\nethereum-keys==0.1.0a7\r\nethereum-serpent==2.0.2\r\nethereum-tester==0.1.0b2\r\nethereum-utils==0.6.0\r\nflake8==3.4.1\r\nflaky==3.4.0\r\nfuture==0.16.0\r\ngraphviz==0.8\r\nhypothesis==3.38.0\r\nidna==2.5\r\nisort==4.2.15\r\njson-rpc==1.10.8\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\nCurrently if we want to use `RLPList` in viper code, we have to install `rlp_decoder` in advance.\r\nLike this\r\n```python\r\nviper_rlp_decoder_tx = rlp.decode(utils.parse_as_bin(\"\"), Transaction)\r\n```\r\nOnce the `rlp_decoder` tx is updated, we have to change the hex manually, otherwise error occurs due to the fact that the address of the contract changes.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nI think it will be better if we introduce a function like `get_rlp_decoder_tx_hex()` in viper, which outputs the hex of the `rlp_decoder` transaction.\r\nThe most simple one like(for simplicity, just assume it is located in the `viper/utils.py`, though it might not be the best location of the function)\r\n```python\r\ndef get_rlp_decoder_tx_hex():\r\n    return \"\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the code which need `rlp_decoder` installing:\r\n```python\r\nviper_rlp_decoder_tx = rlp.decode(utils.parse_as_bin(viper.utils.get_rlp_decoder_tx_hex()), Transaction)\r\nviper_rlp_decoder_addr = viper_rlp_decoder_tx.creates\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n![23905669_813377348856668_3421158803172330292_n](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8223657/33300246-332f6cee-d42a-11e7-9cc3-c7ad1221286d.jpg)\r\n",
